\subsection{Dark diversity fallback}{

Dark diversity is an ecological concept: the set of species that
belong to the regional species pool and could inhabit a site given
its environmental conditions, but have not been observed there. In
TaxaAssign, species with no TaxaExpect prior (e.g., referenced
species not expected at the site) receive a dark diversity prior:
the mean \code{alpha} and \code{beta} from Tier 3 (undetected) rows in
\code{taxaexpect_priors} for the same \code{grid_id} x \code{main_habitat}.
If no site-level Tier 3 rows exist, a global average across all
Tier 3 rows is used. This ensures that every hypothesis has a
non-zero prior, reflecting the possibility that unobserved species
could be present.
}

\subsection{Deduplication and redundancy filtering}{

After the join, rows are deduplicated on \code{observation_id} x
\code{taxon_name} x \code{taxon_name_rank} (keeping the highest
\code{prior_mean}). Genus-rank rows with missing taxonomy are filled
from \code{taxon_name} and propagated from other rows sharing the same
genus. Finally, \code{\link[TaxaMatch:filter_redundant_hypotheses]{TaxaMatch::filter_redundant_hypotheses()}} removes
coarser-rank rows superseded by finer-rank rows in the same
lineage.
}
}
\section{Coarse-rank expansion}{

When a likelihood row has \code{taxon_name_rank} coarser than species (e.g.
\code{"family"} or \code{"genus"}), the primary species-level join finds no match
and the row would otherwise fall back to the global floor prior — ignoring
all species-level prior information within that taxon.

When \code{expansion_taxonomy} is supplied, \code{join_priors()} instead expands each
coarse-rank row into one species-level hypothesis row per retained candidate:
\enumerate{
\item Find all modelled species in \code{taxaexpect_priors} at the focal site ×
habitat that belong to the coarse-rank constraint.
\item Normalize their \code{prior_mean} values within the candidate set.
\item Drop species below \code{expansion_min_prior}.
\item Keep the fewest top species whose cumulative normalized prior
reaches \code{expansion_cumulative_prior}.
\item Replace the coarse-rank row with one row per retained species,
inheriting all likelihood columns unchanged and receiving the
species-level \code{alpha}/\code{beta} priors.
